Description: Smart Queue Management scripts (nftables-native fork)
 Nftables-native fork of sqm-scripts, providing SQM (Smart Queue
 Management) on Linux using CAKE (or fq_codel) as the queue discipline.
 .
 This fork replaces iptables calls with native nft rules, making it a
 clean fit for systems already using nftables/firewall4 as their
 packet-filtering frontend.
 .
 Interfaces are configured via /etc/sqm/<iface>.iface.conf and started
 as instanced systemd units (sqm@<iface>.service).
